      • gettime

        public java.lang.String gettime(java.util.Date s,
                                java.util.Date e,
                                java.lang.String str)
        Parameters:
        s - Date type object that has the time when a course lecture will begin
        e - Date type object that has the time when a course lecture will end
        str - String that stores the venue of the course lecture
        Returns:
        returns a string in the following format "HH1:mm1-HH2:mm2/Venue" where HH1 and mm1 are the class start timings and HH2 and mm2 are the timings at which the class ends

      • gettime2

        public java.lang.String gettime2(java.util.Date s,
                                 java.util.Date e,
                                 java.lang.String str,
                                 java.util.ArrayList<Room> rooms)
        Parameters:
        s - Date type object that has the time when a course lab/tut will begin
        e - Date type object that has the time when a course lab/tut will end
        str - String that stores the day of week when the course lab/tut is scheduled
        rooms - An ArrayList of type rooms that stores the all the venue of lab/tut
        Returns:
        returns a string in the following format "Day_of_week :/HH1:mm1-HH2:mm2/Venue1;venue2...;venueK" where HH1 and mm1 are the lab/tut start timings and HH2 and mm2 are the timings at which the lab/tut ends and venueK is the kth venue of the lab/tut
